                        <interp inst="t18370403-name-1005" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN MILLIS</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep a shoe-shop in Eliza-place, Clerkenwell. About half-past one o'clock, on the 5th of April, I was going from the shop, and saw the prisoner—I had suspicion of him—I watched him—instead of go<lb></lb>ing on he turned back and took these shoes—I followed him nearly as far as Clerkenwell church—he saw me and the policeman following, and threw</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183704030171"></xptr>
               <p>down these shoes into an area, and was taken—the shoes had been just outside the house.</p>
